HEADWORD: Flamboyant
<hw>Flam*boy"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Characterized by waving or flamelike curves, as
in the tracery of windows, etc.; -- said of the later (15th century)
French Gothic style.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

